    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah i've heard about capacitors before. i was reading online that sometimes they just pop or leak. is there any way to tell if it's actually the capacitor causing that weird humming/buzzing sound without opening the whole thing up? also why does it sound so... glitchy? like it's struggling to even start.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you're suspecting a capacitor, there are a few things you can look for without opening up the unit. One way is to listen for a high-pitched noise, which can sometimes indicate a failing capacitor. Another way is to check the unit's voltage with a multimeter. If the voltage is lower than it should be, it could be a sign of a bad capacitor. As for the glitchy sound, it could be due to a failing capacitor struggling to start up the fan. Remember, dealing with electrical components can be dangerous, so it's always best to call a professional if you're unsure. Safety first, my friend!",
